Example
A sinusoidal E-field with amplitude of \( 250 \mathrm{~V} / \mathrm{m} \) and frequency 1 GHz exists in a lossy dielectric medium that has a \( \varepsilon_{r}=2.5 \) and loss tangent of 0.001 . Find the average power dissipated in the medium per cubic meter.
\[
\begin{array}{l}
\tan \delta=0.001=\frac{\sigma}{\omega \varepsilon}=\frac{\sigma}{\omega \varepsilon_{0} \varepsilon_{\mathrm{r}}}=\frac{\sigma}{\left(2 \pi \cdot 10^{9}\right)\left(\frac{10^{-9}}{36 \pi}\right)(2.5)} \\
\sigma=1.39 \cdot 10^{-4} \mathrm{~S} / \mathrm{m}
\end{array}
\]

The average power dissipated per unit volume is
