E_{o i}\left(\frac{\cos \theta_{i}}{\eta_{1}}-\frac{\cos \theta_{t}}{\eta_{2}}\right)=E_{o r}\left(\frac{\cos \theta_{t}}{\eta_{2}}+\frac{\cos \theta_{i}}{\eta_{1}}\right) \\
E_{o i}\left(\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}-\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}\right)=E_{o r}\left(\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}-\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}\right) \\
\frac{E_{o r}}{E_{o i}}=\frac{\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}-\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}}{\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}+\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}} \equiv \Gamma_{\perp}
\end{array}
\]

This is the reflection coefficient for the perpendicular polarization. It is a function of the angle of incidence, along with the properties of the media, of course.

From Eqn.(11.6), and divide \( \mathrm{E}_{\mathrm{oi}} \) in all the terms:
\[
\begin{array}{l}
1+\frac{E_{o r}}{E_{o i}}=\frac{E_{o t}}{E_{o i}} \\
1+\Gamma_{\perp}=\tau_{\perp}
\end{array}
\]

The \( \tau \) in this equation is called the transmission coefficient. The perpendicular sign is kept there to remind us this equation is only correct for the perpendicular polarization. Substitute \( \Gamma \) from Eqn.(11.7), we have:
\[
\tau_{\perp}=1+\Gamma_{\perp}=1+\frac{\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}-\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}}{\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}+\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}}=\frac{2 \eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}}{\eta_{2} \cos \theta_{i}+\eta_{1} \cos \theta_{t}}
\]

The wave impedance \( \eta \) is related to the index of refraction n. Again:
\[
\begin{array}{l}
\eta=\sqrt{\frac{\mu}{\varepsilon}}=\sqrt{\frac{\mu_{o} \mu_{r}}{\varepsilon_{o} \varepsilon_{r}}}=\eta_{o} \sqrt{\frac{\mu_{r}}{\varepsilon_{r}}} \\
n=\frac{c}{v}=\sqrt{\frac{\mu \varepsilon}{\mu_{o} \varepsilon_{o}}}=\sqrt{\mu_{r} \varepsilon_{r}}
\end{array}
\]

Only in non-magnetic medium (which is all we deal with in the course) that they reduce to: \( n=\sqrt{\varepsilon_{r}} \), and \( \eta=\frac{\eta_{o}}{\sqrt{\varepsilon_{r}}}=\frac{\eta_{o}}{n} \). So, the coefficients can be re-written as (in a nonmagnetic medium):
\[
\Gamma_{\perp}=\frac{\frac{\eta_{o}}{n_{2}} \cos \theta_{i}-\frac{\eta_{o}}{n_{1}} \cos \theta_{t}}{\frac{\eta_{o}}{n_{2}} \cos \theta_{i}+\frac{\eta_{o}}{n_{1}} \cos \theta_{t}}=\frac{n_{1} \cos \theta_{i}-n_{2} \cos \theta_{t}}{n_{1} \cos \theta_{i}+n_{2} \cos \theta_{t}}
\]

